Labour leader Ed Miliband says he will 'abolish' the 200-year-old rule for non-domicile status which allows people to only pay tax on UK income . 
  He says it makes Britain an 'offshore tax haven for a few' and can 'no longer be justified' Labour would allow 'real temporary residents' to take advantage of the rules . 
  Shadow chancellor Ed Balls warned in January it would cost the country money . 
  Duncan Bannatyne has backed the Labour tax crackdown . 
 